The paper deals with the integration of structured and unstructured data for Artificial Intelligence, which is a common theme in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The specific task of Entity Linking is a natural language processing task, which falls under the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a novel approach that combines symbolic information with neural networks, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the problem of constructing a type system, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on standard datasets, which is a common theme in the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
